            <title>[HIVE-25190] BytesColumnVector fails when the aggregate size is &gt; 1gb</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HIVE-25190</link>
                <project id="12310843" key="HIVE">Hive</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Currently, BytesColumnVector will allocate a buffer for small values (&amp;lt; 1mb), but fail with:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; RuntimeException(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;Overflow of newLength. smallBuffer.length=&quot;&lt;/span&gt;
                + smallBuffer.length + &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;, nextElemLength=&quot;&lt;/span&gt; + nextElemLength);
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;if the aggregate size of the buffer crosses over 1gb. &lt;/p&gt;</description>
